              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="basic-form" onclick="myFunction(event)">Standard Posture</li>
                <li>Feet - The heels are slightly wider than shoulder width. Point your toes at an angle to the outside!
                  There are individual differences, so perform actively in a position where the knees do not converge
                </li>
                <li>Knee direction - set to face the same direction as the toe</li>
                <li>Center of gravity - located at the rear (heel side)</li>
                <li>Spinal Neutral - The lower back is always neutral through abdominal pressure</li>
                <li>Abdominal pressure - increase abdominal pressure through abdominal breathing and give strength to
                  the abdomen</li>
                <li>Hip joint - Focus on sitting vertically with the hip joint pulled back slightly</li> -> If the hip
                is pulled back too much, the back is bent too much and the burden on the lower back increases
                <li>Hip fold - Perform consciously so that the hip joint is folded</li> -> Easy, vertical descent with
                the center of the body behind
                <li>Simultaneous extension - Conscious of simultaneous extension of the knee, thigh, and hip joint</li>
                <li>힘 - 위쪽 허벅지와 고관절에 힘이 들어가도록 의식</li>
                <br>
                <li>Respiration - Inhale (inhale) then go down, then come up and exhale (exhale). Immediately after
                  inhalation, go down, then come up and exhale. repeat</li>
                <li>! butt wink. When squatting down, the pelvis rolls toward the floor, causing the lumbar spine to be
                  rounded</li>
                <li>! Good morning posture. If your hips come up faster than your upper body, you will be in a posture
                  like bowing down and saying hello. This is bad for your back, so be careful</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="benefit">
                Very effective for overall Lower Body and Upper Body
              </div>
